üü¶ 1. GOLDEN MANIFEST DOCTRINE

The foundational law of model identity in PantheonOS

The Golden Manifest is:
	‚Ä¢	The canonical, immutable, cryptographically sealed record of a model‚Äôs true identity.
	‚Ä¢	The only source of truth about what a model is allowed to be.
	‚Ä¢	The anchor for Hades, Blacksmith, Merkle Warden, and the Kernel.

Once created, it must never change.
Any model that does not match its Golden Manifest is immediately QUARANTINED.

Golden Law:

A model may speak only if it matches the Golden Manifest that defines its being.

This is the Pantheon-Prime equivalent of a bios certificate or a zero-knowledge identity attestation.

‚∏ª

üü• 2. GOLDEN MANIFEST SPECIFICATION (TECHNICAL)

2.1 File Format

The manifest MUST be encoded as one of:
	‚Ä¢	golden_manifest.json
	‚Ä¢	golden_manifest.toml
	‚Ä¢	golden_manifest.yaml

JSON is canonical.

‚∏ª

2.2 JSON Schema v1.0

{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
  "title": "Pantheon Golden Manifest",
  "type": "object",
  "required": [
    "model_id",
    "name",
    "owner",
    "version",
    "path",
    "format",
    "arch_hash",
    "param_hash",
    "created_at",
    "created_by",
    "status"
  ],
  "properties": {
    "model_id": { "type": "string" },
    "name": { "type": "string" },
    "owner": { "type": "string" },
    "version": { "type": "string" },
    "path": { "type": "string" },
    "format": {
      "type": "string",
      "enum": ["safetensors", "torchscript", "onnx", "frozen"]
    },
    "arch_hash": { "type": "string", "description": "SHA256 hash of architecture bytes" },
    "param_hash": { "type": "string", "description": "SHA256 hash of raw parameter bytes" },
    "created_at": { "type": "string" },
    "created_by": { "type": "string" },
    "status": {
      "type": "string",
      "enum": ["ACTIVE", "QUARANTINED", "BLOCKED"]
    },
    "last_verified_at": { "type": ["string", "null"] },
    "last_verified_by": { "type": ["string", "null"] },
    "signatures": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["signer", "signature", "algorithm"],
        "properties": {
          "signer": { "type": "string" },
          "signature": { "type": "string" },
          "algorithm": { "type": "string" }
        }
      }
    },
    "notes": { "type": ["string", "null"] }
  }
}


