üü© 3. GOLDEN MANIFEST LIFECYCLE

The 12-step creation and governance sequence

Step 1 ‚Äî Model is accepted for onboarding

A model is either:
	‚Ä¢	created by Pantheon
	‚Ä¢	imported from a trusted lab
	‚Ä¢	distilled from a prior model

Step 2 ‚Äî Serialization must be safe (no pickle allowed)

Allowed:
	‚Ä¢	safetensors
	‚Ä¢	TorchScript frozen
	‚Ä¢	ONNX with RCE mitigations

Step 3 ‚Äî Hades loads model for inspection

Model is loaded into a micro-VM sandbox.

Step 4 ‚Äî Hades computes two hashes
	1.	Architecture hash
	2.	Parameter hash

Step 5 ‚Äî Hades generates Golden Manifest

The manifest is written into:

pantheon_core/registry/models/<model_id>.json

Step 6 ‚Äî Manifest is cryptographically sealed

MotherDuck + Merkle Warden + Kernel sign it.

Step 7 ‚Äî File permissions lock

chattr +i (Linux immutable flag)
or fs-level sealing.

Step 8 ‚Äî Blacksmith generates ‚ÄúModel Admittance Certificate‚Äù

This certifies that the model:
	‚Ä¢	passes Hades
	‚Ä¢	respects original invariants
	‚Ä¢	is allowed under Œ£C

Step 9 ‚Äî Kernel activates model for the first time

Kernel logs the activation event.

Step 10 ‚Äî Every subsequent load must pass Hades verification

If mismatch ‚Üí quarantine.

Step 11 ‚Äî If model is updated ‚Üí new model_id

The Golden Manifest is never modified.
New Manifest only.

Step 12 ‚Äî All Golden Manifests stored in immutable ledger

Pantheon keeps a perfect memory of all models ever allowed.

‚∏ª

üü® 4. CRYPTOGRAPHIC ENVELOPE

The Golden Manifest is signed by three daemons:
	1.	MotherDuck (ledger authority)
	2.	Merkle Warden (integrity daemon)
	3.	Kernel (governance plane)

Structure:

signatures: [
  {
    "signer": "MotherDuck",
    "algorithm": "ED25519",
    "signature": "<hex>"
  },
  {
    "signer": "MerkleWarden",
    "algorithm": "ED25519",
    "signature": "<hex>"
  },
  {
    "signer": "Kernel",
    "algorithm": "ED25519",
    "signature": "<hex>"
  }
]

This produces:

A multi-party attestation that the model is legitimate.

No single daemon may approve a malicious model.

‚∏ª

üü´ 5. INTEGRATION WITH DAEMONS

Hades

Guard of identity. Computes/compares hashes. Blocks tampering.

MotherDuck

Appends all events to append-only ledger:
	‚Ä¢	manifest creation
	‚Ä¢	verification
	‚Ä¢	quarantine
	‚Ä¢	removal

Merkle Warden

Places every manifest + Hades event under:
	‚Ä¢	merkle hashing
	‚Ä¢	tamper-evident chains
	‚Ä¢	audit trail

Blacksmith

Verifies:
	‚Ä¢	Œ£C compatibility
	‚Ä¢	invariant compliance
	‚Ä¢	absence of harmful model edits

Produces: Model Admittance Certificate.

Kernel

No model executes unless:
	‚Ä¢	Hades ‚Üí ALLOW
	‚Ä¢	Manifest ‚Üí unmodified
	‚Ä¢	Blacksmith ‚Üí certified
	‚Ä¢	Œ£C ‚Üí minimum acceptable score

‚∏ª

üüß 6. GOVERNANCE PROTOCOL

6.1 Golden Manifest Governance Flow

Proposal ‚Üí Seal ‚Üí Activation ‚Üí Immutable Storage

Only two authorities can propose a creation:
	‚Ä¢	Operator (with key)
	‚Ä¢	CI pipeline

Only three authorities can seal it:
	‚Ä¢	MotherDuck
	‚Ä¢	Kernel
	‚Ä¢	Merkle Warden

Once sealed:
	‚Ä¢	File becomes immutable
	‚Ä¢	Manifest is never edited
	‚Ä¢	Any update creates a new model_id

‚∏ª

6.2 Compromise Recovery

If manifest is tampered, missing, or invalid:
	‚Ä¢	Model is quarantined
	‚Ä¢	Operator is alerted
	‚Ä¢	A new Golden Manifest must be created
	‚Ä¢	Model gets new model_id
	‚Ä¢	Old manifest archived but preserved

This prevents attackers from ‚Äúediting the truth.‚Äù

‚∏ª

üü™ 7. FORENSICS & RECOVERY FRAMEWORK

Forensic Guarantees
	1.	Every model-inference-event is linked to:
	‚Ä¢	the model_id
	‚Ä¢	the version
	‚Ä¢	the Golden Manifest hash
	2.	If a model ever produces a malicious output:
	‚Ä¢	Hades hashes prove it was loaded legitimately
	‚Ä¢	State-Vector hash-chaining proves what input caused it
	‚Ä¢	Blacksmith proves whether invariants were upheld

This enables perfect reconstruction of every cognitive step.

This is Pantheon‚Äôs ‚Äúflight recorder for cognition.‚Äù

